Dialogue: 10,0:00:20.68,0:00:24.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Willow trees overlook the front gates of the Yoshiwara district. {okay, this one has an even more obsolete language, it's more unintelligible than chinese >_>}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:25.42,0:00:27.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Though it's the Meiji era,\N it continues to be
Dialogue: 10,0:00:27.90,0:00:31.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,one of the few red-light districts\N licensed since the Edo period.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:32.95,0:00:39.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The entrance bustles with busy people,\N and the rickshaw traffic is heavy here.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.26,0:00:45.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This district is named after the Daionji Temple and should be distinctly Buddhist,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:45.58,0:00:48.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but it is inhabited by carefree people.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:02.14,0:01:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one should I get?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:03.73,0:01:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This one!{それがいい}{"This is good/Those are good/This one is good", it's the little girl choosing one}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:04.71,0:01:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.{basan}{はいよ}{"Here you go/Alright", it's the grandma giving them those balls}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:04.71,0:01:06.08,Overlap,,0,0,0,,I want this one!{kid}{あたしこれ}{"I want this one", it's the kid picking one}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:07.74,0:01:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This should pay for everything. \NKeep the change.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:10.63,0:01:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you as always.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:13.35,0:01:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls, you should all thank Midori.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:15.98,0:01:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Midori!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:17.68,0:01:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? She's pretty generous for a child\N whose kimono sleeves are still tucked in. {kataage = tuck at the shoulder (of a child's clothes); shoulder tuck​; "kataage wo toru" = idiomatic for "coming of age"}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:21.97,0:01:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's thanks to her older sister Omaki,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:24.15,0:01:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who works at Daikoku, a prosperous brothel.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:26.95,0:01:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's no surprise she can be generous.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:29.69,0:01:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go.{さあ行こ}{"Now, let's go", the kid inviting the others to go, presumably}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.38,0:01:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I look forward to seeing what she grows up to be.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.20,0:01:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet she'll be even prettier than Omaki.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.65,0:01:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We're so lucky.{おいらたちは，ねえ}{very vague sentence, but that girl is talking about the group and implying something about their situation, most likely the most recent event which are the balls}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.65,0:01:41.24,Overlap,,0,0,0,,I really wanted this one{or more generally, "One of these"}!{それがあたし欲しかったんだ}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.24,0:01:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, really?{わぁ，よかった}{よかった functions as a "good for you/glad it worked out/that's great" kind of phrase}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.83,0:01:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.18,0:02:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Look out!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.33,0:02:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No spacing out!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.48,0:02:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:10.38,0:02:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, let me clean that off.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.06,0:02:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No need. You'll stain your towel.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.69,0:02:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What rude people\N those rickshaw drivers are!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:19.20,0:02:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, but you really don't have to.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.61,0:02:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look at the couple! {ofutari-san}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.86,0:02:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You look good together!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:25.58,0:02:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What a sight! The temple monk and the Daikoku geisha together!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.67,0:02:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes sense. Better to call dibs on her now, before she's
Dialogue: 10,0:02:33.44,0:02:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a full-fledged Daikoku geisha and the talk of the town!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.17,0:02:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Wait, Shin! \NYou still have mud on you!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.54,0:02:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're the son \Nof the corrupt head monk,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.00,0:02:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,no wonder you're too shy \Nto show your face on the street!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.24,0:02:58.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It wasn't Shin of Ryuge Temple's fault that he acted so curt.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.82,0:03:01.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When he heard something so detestable,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.49,0:03:04.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,his upright character wouldn't let him act otherwise.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:04.33,0:03:06.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He couldn't bear to hear that
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.82,0:03:09.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,about the father who had brought him up.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.10,0:03:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Bunji? Ushimatsu's here too. Come on in.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.99,0:03:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! Kids from the main-street gang were that disrespectful to a Ryuge Temple monk? {???? originally was "from Shota's gang" - dunno what this is about, but dunno what omotemachi is either; there is a "back-street gang" in the book, the one led by this guy chokichi, so the other's gotta be the "main street gang"}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:28.11,0:03:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I bet they knew Shin was with our back-street gang. That's why they did it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.65,0:03:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. Maybe them making the first move was a blessing in disguise.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.65,0:03:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Chokichi! You better not start\N any more fights!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.76,0:03:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.34,0:03:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We can give them what for \Nat the next festival.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.17,0:03:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't do that, I, who dragged Shin
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.62,0:03:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,into my back-street gang by force, \Nwill lose face!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.98,0:03:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to swaying the Ryuge monks, even the guys who bowed
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.13,0:04:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to Shota before are flocking to the back-street gang!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.75,0:04:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, we're not backing down!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.68,0:04:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, guys. Even if Shota's got\N the best grades or his parents are rich,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.53,0:04:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the pawnshop they're running is a racket!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.05,0:04:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All their pawnshop does is suck money out
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.01,0:04:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of honest working people with extortionate loans!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.70,0:04:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Beating him to death \Nwould be a favor to society.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.36,0:04:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Chokichi! Don't you plan any fights! {lit: no violence}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.72,0:04:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.41,0:04:32.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At that time, Shotaro was still unaware of the danger that lurked nearby. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.72,0:04:35.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He visited Midori at the Daikoku Brothel
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.86,0:04:41.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to discuss their plans for the upcoming festival and how to make the most of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:42.53,0:04:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! We could make a magic lantern!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.24,0:04:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be wonderful! \NEveryone could enjoy it!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.15,0:04:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get some of the stuff \Nfrom my place.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.47,0:04:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Midori can buy everything else at the stationary store.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.67,0:05:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I can be the photographer,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.22,0:05:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and Sangoro from the back-street gang can narrate. {?????????????}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.42,0:05:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Sangoro would be the perfect narrator.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.68,0:05:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And his face is sure \Nto make it even funnier!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.24,0:05:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine! Let's get everyone properly excited for the festival. {??????}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.91,0:05:18.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shotaro attended the public school,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.63,0:05:24.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,while Shin and Midori went\N to Ikueisha, a private school.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.18,0:05:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.85,0:05:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know the name\N of this beautiful flower?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.56,0:05:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:35.63,0:05:40.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shin gave a snappy answer because\N he was worried the kids would see him
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.98,0:05:43.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with Midori again and make fun of him.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.04,0:05:47.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But Midori knew nothing of this,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.29,0:05:50.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,so naturally, she rashly decided
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.70,0:05:54.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that she would never even so much as greet him again.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.26,0:06:08.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Senzoku Festival \Nwas held on August 20.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.57,0:06:12.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In it, various towns tried to outdo each other in the showiness of their floats. {festival float; portable shrine dedicated to a god and shaped like a house; dancing platform​}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.74,0:06:15.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The traders from Nihonzutsumi to Kuruwa
Dialogue: 10,0:06:15.21,0:06:18.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and their toys captured the attention of the kids right away,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.97,0:06:22.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,making the festival even more exciting.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.34,0:06:28.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This year, Shotaro didn't join in \Nthe festival chorus, {bakabayashi = orchestra present at Japanese festival; festival music (may be sung from a festival float)}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.03,0:06:31.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and he spent the eve of the festival \Nquietly with his friends.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.08,0:06:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They're late.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.95,0:06:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What's keeping Midori?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.14,0:06:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't start until she \Nand Sangoro get here.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.69,0:07:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I'm late. \NI was babysitting my little brother.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.19,0:07:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sangoro! For being late, \Nyou have to go get Midori now!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.54,0:07:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Me?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.70,0:07:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Now stop arguing and get going!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.20,0:07:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya got it! Have no fear! {???????????? this episode is fucking vile}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.63,0:07:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, everyone's waiting! \NHurry up! {maybe this mother is the head geisha, not her biological mother}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.39,0:07:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right. I'm trying, \Nbut the festival only comes once a year.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.48,0:07:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to be as beautiful as possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.76,0:07:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Midori, hurry up!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.90,0:07:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Fleeting is the hidden love... {I found definiteion of shinobu koiji as the traditional song, but I couldnt find the lyrics, this episode if fucking cursed; hidden love = one you never confess}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.65,0:07:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But next time I see her... {???????}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.21,0:07:56.55,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Oh my, Shota. You're barely thirteen.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.55,0:07:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The path of love is still ahead for you. {????? lit: can't get your guard down}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.65,0:08:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go get Midori! \NCome with me, people!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.17,0:08:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are, Shota!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.67,0:08:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been calling you! \NWhy didn't you come home for dinner?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.32,0:08:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.02,0:08:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.51,0:08:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry, kids. You can come over\N and play with him later.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.77,0:08:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.44,0:08:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.26,0:08:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're kidding!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.78,0:08:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You made my Shin the underboss of your back-street gang? {taisho = general}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.83,0:08:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I truly feel sorry for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.13,0:08:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,With him around, \Nthe atmosphere dampens at once. {smelling of incense; overly pious}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.87,0:08:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even today, he talked to me \Nabout not drinking and eating eel,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:49.00,0:08:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,about the virtues of poverty.\NLook, he's lecturing me! {lit: and how money-making is erroneous}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:52.50,0:08:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent him to a store in Tamachi \Njust to get rid of him.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.26,0:09:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean he'll be late today?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.42,0:09:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. If I'd known you were coming,\N I wouldn't have sent him away.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.43,0:09:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But I guess he'd be gone for the Buddhist lantern festival anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.09,0:09:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Chokichi,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.57,0:09:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,aren't festivals made for everyone to get rowdy once in a while? {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.30,0:09:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Go out and enjoy yourself\N as much as you can.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.83,0:09:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Show them the spirit \Nof the back-street gang.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.00,0:09:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Will do, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.32,0:09:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,After all that panting and rushing over, \Nthis is beyond anticlimactic! {/like the fire went out}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.43,0:09:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To be fair to Shota, his grandmother is the only family he has.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.24,0:09:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And she came all the way \Nover here just to get him.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:43.93,0:09:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll be back right after dinner.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.07,0:09:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.52,0:09:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what would you say to a lively rehearsal of our Yoshiwara impromptu skit?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:55.18,0:09:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you slowly look around you \Nat the heyday of your life, {????????????? only finding another stupid song with similar lyrics}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.92,0:10:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the paper lanterns shine cheerfully, \Nhanging off the eaves of homes. {????????}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.58,0:10:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're always so bright and... {???????}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:03.21,0:10:05.71,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Sangoro, you there? Hey, Sangoro!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.71,0:10:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out here! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:07.74,0:10:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.63,0:10:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You dirty two-timer!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.41,0:10:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Blinded by money, you think you can pull all this crap?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.91,0:10:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You traitor of the back-street gang! {??????}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.32,0:10:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Get him!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.87,0:10:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Shota, come out and fight!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.35,0:10:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Chokichi, will face you!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.59,0:10:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, stop hiding!\NWhat's the matter?!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.63,0:10:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sh-Shota's not here.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.68,0:10:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You bastard! If you're covering up for him, I'll kill you!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.28,0:10:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I swear! He's not here!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.05,0:10:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine! I don't care anymore.\NLet's get them all!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.04,0:10:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.54,0:10:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it! You can't fight in here! Get out!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.46,0:10:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Tch! Shut up!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:54.17,0:10:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, give us Shota!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.68,0:10:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's he hiding? Tell me!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.23,0:10:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk! {言け}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.64,0:11:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.43,0:11:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.94,0:11:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay out of it, Midori.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.75,0:11:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Chokichi, Sangoro never did\N anything to you!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.62,0:11:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to fight Shota, \Ndon't drag everyone else into it.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:10.22,0:11:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't run away, and he's not hiding. He's just not here.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.26,0:11:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking it out on Sangoro is just awful!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.48,0:11:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want someone to fight,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.94,0:11:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have a grudge, \Nthen take it out on me, you coward!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.88,0:11:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that? \NShut your mouth, you whore!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.87,0:11:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Young man! How dare you\N say that to Midori?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.39,0:11:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Tch! She'll just grow up to be a whore \Nlike her sister, so who cares?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.71,0:11:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.71,0:11:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've done it, Chokichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.72,0:11:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Serves you right.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.22,0:11:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't like it,\N come fight us anytime.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.84,0:11:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But watch out, 'cause Shin\N of Ryuge Temple is with us!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.12,0:11:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He is?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:48.66,0:11:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Tch! The front-street gang are all chickens!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.70,0:11:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap! It's the police!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.35,0:11:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sangoro! If you're quitting the gang, \Nthen watch your back!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.18,0:12:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is unusual. \NYou don't usually skip school.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.24,0:12:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like snow on a summer day.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.47,0:12:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want breakfast,\N how about we order some sushi later?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.61,0:12:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to the shrine. {oinari = shrine (shinto) - not temple (buddgist)}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.73,0:12:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I could go for you \Nif you're not feeling well.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.42,0:12:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who's been praying for my sister's prosperity.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.19,0:12:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to go myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.67,0:13:06.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The day the festival ended, \NMidori skipped school.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.75,0:13:11.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She could wash the mud\N from her forehead easily,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.54,0:13:13.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but she could never erase the shame from her heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.18,0:13:20.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Everyone knew how violent\N Chokichi could be,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.14,0:13:25.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but without Shin's backing, he wouldn't have dared to go that far, she thought.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.64,0:13:27.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even though Shin was older,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.74,0:13:31.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,a young master of the Ryuge Temple\N with an outstanding academic record,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.14,0:13:35.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Midori wouldn't see him, even to give him \Na single sheet of paper.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.04,0:13:47.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She thought, "My sister Omaki,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.15,0:13:49.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,a celebrated courtesan at Daikoku,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.15,0:13:53.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,is well off now, despite coming from a family that had fallen into poverty at one point. {?????????????????????????????? I wanna spike the author or whoever decided to include this narration verbatim; they keep saying zensei throughout this episode but I haven't a fucking clue, not even any suspicions what it may be}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.02,0:13:56.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I'm lucky I can live in the Daikoku dorm
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.91,0:13:59.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and look after it when everyone's gone." {????????}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.16,0:14:01.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Unwilling to tolerate Chokichi's injustice,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.45,0:14:04.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and too vexed by the Ryuge monks now bothering her,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.62,0:14:08.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Midori suddenly stopped attending school.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.27,0:14:14.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She spent her days in the company\N of her close friends, doing nothing. {/playing}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.51,0:14:28.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Shin was disturbed
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.04,0:14:32.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,by the festival incident, \Nwhich surpassed his worst fears.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.40,0:14:35.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It happened while he was away,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.66,0:14:40.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,so there was no use blaming them now\N for the things done in his name.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.40,0:14:45.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Still, he was overwhelmed by the feeling of guilt
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.20,0:14:48.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,for the pain inflicted \Non Midori and Sangoro.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.67,0:14:54.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The summer finally ended.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.92,0:15:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? I thought I just heard someone stepping on the planks outside.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.10,0:15:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Really? Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.51,0:15:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.83,0:15:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I called him, but he wouldn't come. \NHe was just passing through. {unsure, maybe "he wouldn't come even if I called"}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.11,0:15:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it Shin?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.57,0:15:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a shame.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.74,0:15:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If he came in,\N it'd only be to bully someone,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.70,0:15:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but he ran away\N when he heard we were here. {?????????????}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.18,0:15:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's cold!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.36,0:15:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Midori, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.08,0:15:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.13,0:15:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be pitiful as a priest.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.36,0:15:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He acts all meek in public,\N but behind the scenes,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.15,0:16:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he's been egging Chokichi \Nand the others on to do awful things.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.13,0:16:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never met anyone so twisted, spiteful, and mean-spirited!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.63,0:16:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But I heard that Shin didn't know anything about the festival fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.25,0:16:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Who told you that?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.95,0:16:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Chokichi apologized to Shin at school.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.10,0:16:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He was making up excuses,\N but he was sorry for starting the fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.38,0:16:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And Shin said,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.07,0:16:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"What's done is done, \Nbut don't pick on the weak anymore."
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.78,0:16:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it was shameful\N to bully Sangoro and Midori.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.22,0:16:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll probably rain all day.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.46,0:16:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.94,0:16:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, lend me some cloth. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.20,0:16:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone tore a sandal outside.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.32,0:17:07.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When he realized he was passing by Midori's house,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.48,0:17:09.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shin remembered what happened, became distressed,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:09.72,0:17:12.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and tried to hurry past it, \Nbut unfortunately,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.47,0:17:15.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the rain had weakened the thong on his sandal. {??????}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.27,0:17:17.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The embarrassment was\N already unbearable.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.30,0:17:20.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then he heard footsteps \Nskipping across stepping stones,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.57,0:17:24.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and he felt as if a bucket of cold water \Nhad been poured over him.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.02,0:17:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Midori, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:30.82,0:17:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back in. You'll catch a cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.69,0:17:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.57,0:17:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Shin, what happened to you?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.47,0:18:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to my sister's place \Nto deliver something,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.36,0:18:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but my sandal broke, so I'm stuck here.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.14,0:18:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, take mine. Here.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.31,0:18:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take yours home and store them.\N Come on, hand them over. {?????????? lit: throw them into the kitchen - no clue what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.18,0:18:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But I feel bad about this.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:16.13,0:18:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it. I'm used to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.74,0:18:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.94,0:18:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.49,0:18:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Shota? Not collecting the interest today? {lit: did you take a day off the daily installment - we know they are a pawn shop/loan sharks so ig it's something about collecting the loans}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.73,0:18:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen Midori?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:50.87,0:18:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been looking for her all day.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.34,0:18:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw her passing by my house earlier. \NShe was going over the drawbridge.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.36,0:19:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So she was going into Yoshiwara? {lit: go in - doesn't say what}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.61,0:19:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it was nothing like usual, Shota!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.29,0:19:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Her hair was all done up, \Na full-blown pompadour!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.65,0:19:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe she's about to become a geisha? {oiran = prostitute}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:09.82,0:19:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to the dorm. {presumably [of the daikoku]??? he ends up going to her house so idk}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.25,0:19:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,She sure is pretty.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.92,0:19:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that you, Shota?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.72,0:19:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Midori?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.64,0:19:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In the back.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.85,0:19:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Midori?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.44,0:19:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Midori?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.74,0:19:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that hairdo looks really nice on you.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.24,0:19:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you feeling okay, Midori?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.36,0:19:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been in a bad mood \Nsince this morning. {as opposed to being ill}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.46,0:19:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you try to cheer her up, Shota?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.25,0:19:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to start steaming the rice now.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:56.31,0:19:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you have a fight \Nwith your sister?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.51,0:20:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? \NDid I say something wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.23,0:20:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, tell me!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:08.36,0:20:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to grow up.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.31,0:20:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go back in time a year or two.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:12.78,0:20:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you talking about that now? {lit: why are you saying something so impossible}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.74,0:20:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go back.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:15.90,0:20:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're acting weird.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:18.65,0:20:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave me alone, Shota!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.44,0:20:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Midori!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.45,0:20:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm begging you to leave, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:24.70,0:20:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you so angry?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.95,0:20:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to see anyone anymore! \NOr talk to anyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.24,0:20:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I said go away!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:35.07,0:20:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I was such a bother!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.64,0:20:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting next year, everyone in the back-\nstreet gang will switch to your side.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.39,0:20:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, if Shin goes to some Buddhist monk school,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.47,0:21:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Chokichi will lose his right-hand man, \Nand it'll be a piece of cake.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.52,0:21:17.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,From that day on, Midori had suddenly become much more mature.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:17.08,0:21:21.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She went to the red-light district to take lessons from her sister,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:21.02,0:21:24.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and she stopped going out to play.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.46,0:21:29.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The front street now felt deserted, \Nas if the fire had gone out. {shota's gang's namesake}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.25,0:22:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:04.11,0:22:10.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was finally the day for Shin to leave, to go far away,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.26,0:22:12.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and learn how to be a full-fledged priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.08,0:22:37.94,Song,,0,0,0,,I write a letter to my loved one
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.64,0:22:44.86,Song,,0,0,0,,I write and tear it, tear it, and write again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.86,0:22:51.41,Song,,0,0,0,,I throw the rolled up paper at the window
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.41,0:22:58.58,Song,,0,0,0,,It's raining outside, just like the tears on my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.69,0:23:06.46,Song,,0,0,0,,Life is a sea, youth is a boat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.46,0:23:13.53,Song,,0,0,0,,My love, please come and save me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.53,0:23:15.95,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.84,0:23:19.06,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.70,0:23:27.21,Song,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm sinking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.21,0:23:36.63,Song,,0,0,0,,Not a single star in sight, in the sea of ​​sadness
